article.description: — Kalib Boone scored 24 points, six in overtime, and Rob Whaley Jr. scored seven of his nine in the extra period to lead UNLV over 75-69 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Boone, Whaley lead UNLV to 75-69 OT win over Wyoming
article.linkText: Boone, Whaley lead UNLV to 75-69 OT win over Wyoming
article.story: LARAMIE, Wyo. -- — Kalib Boone scored 24 points, six in overtime, and Rob Whaley Jr. scored seven of his nine in the extra period to lead UNLV over 75-69 on Tuesday night. Boone also added 12 rebounds for the Rebels (17-10, 10-5 Mountain West Conference). Dedan Thomas Jr. scored 13 points while shooting 5 for 17, including 2 for 4 from beyond the arc. Justin Webster shot 3 of 5 from the field and 3 for 3 from the line to finish with 11 points. The Cowboys (13-15, 6-9) were led in scoring by Brendan Wenzel, who finished with 20 points, including four 3-pointers. Wyoming also got 13 points from Sam Griffin. Mason Walters finished with 12 points and seven rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
